  yi = c(0.92, 4.42, 1.13, 2.11, 1.47, 1.00, 0.94, 2.63, 0.96, 1.47, 1.85, 1.01),  # Risk ratios
  vi = c((1.30 - 0.65)/3.92, (4.30 - 0.65)/3.92, (1.70 - 0.71)/3.92, (2.71 - 1.64)/3.92,
         (1.53 - 1.16)/3.92, (1.63 - 0.59)/3.92, (1.11 - 0.80)/3.92,

         (2.29 - 1.09)/3.92, (1.56 - 0.56)/3.92)^2,
  year = c(2008, 2010, 2015, 2017, 2017, 2018, 2019, 2021, 2021, 2022, 2022, 2024)
)

# Function for Meta-Analysis and Meta-Regression
run_meta_analysis <- function(data, outcome_name) {
  # Meta-Analysis
  meta <- rma(yi, vi, data = data, method = "REML")
  print(paste("Meta-analysis Summary for", outcome_name, ":"))
  print(summary(meta))
  
  # Meta-Regression
  meta_reg <- rma(yi, vi, mods = ~ year, data = data, method = "REML")
  print(paste("Meta-regression Summary for", outcome_name, "with Year as Moderator:"))
  print(summary(meta_reg))
  
  # Plotting
  pred <- predict(meta_reg, newmods = seq(min(data$year), max(data$year), length=100))
  plot(data$year, data$yi, pch=19, xlab="Year", ylab="Effect Size",
       main=paste("Meta-Regression Plot for", outcome_name))
  lines(seq(min(data$year), max(data$year), length=100), pred$pred, col="blue", lwd=2)
  lines(seq(min(data$year), max(data$year), length=100), pred$ci.lb, col="blue", lty="dashed")
  lines(seq(min(data$year), max(data$year), length=100), pred$ci.ub, col="blue", lty="dashed")
}

# Run Meta-Analysis and Meta-Regression for Each Outcome
outcomes <- list("J-CTO Outcome" = data_jcto, "Total Procedure Time" = data_proc_time,
                 "Total Fluoroscopy Time" = data_fluoro_time, "Contrast Volume" = data_contrast_volume,
                 "Target Lesion (LCX)" = data_target_lesion)

for (outcome in names(outcomes)) {
  run_meta_analysis(outcomes[[outcome]], outcome)
}
